(secondQuint)The Effects of Different Interior Decorations in a Psychiatric Intensive Care Unit.

.

 The PICU in Ostmarka psychiatric department, St.

 Olavs Hospital contains 2 identical parts.

 Each part contains 2 beds.

 The PICU had a traditional sparsely decorated interior.

 In cooperation with architects and the county building authorities one of the parts were redecorated to an interior like an ordinary Norwegian home.

 All patients admitted the the PICU were semi-randomized to either traditional or "Norwegian home" interior decorations.

 Symptoms, behaviour, and treatment were evaluated at admittance, day 3 and discharge from the PICU.

 The Effects of Different Interior Decorations in a Psychiatric Intensive Care Unit.

@highlight

The purpose of the study is to compare effects of treatment of patients acutely admitted to a Psychiatric Intensive Care Unit (PICU) with either a sparsely decorated interior or interior decorations like an ordinary, Norwegian home.

